definition: many/much/often/a lot of/numerous/more/in excess/how (to what extent)/multi-/Taiwan pr. [duo2] when it means "how"

sentences.english: Since founded more than 20 years ago, we put all our efforts on produce high quality multi-functional tools.
sentences.chinese: 本公司建廠二十多年來不斷專注於開拓高質量的產品。

sentences.english: But that was over twenty years ago.
sentences.chinese: 但那是二十多年前的事情了。

sentences.english: Aside from my room, there are two dozens of rooms in this courtyard.
sentences.chinese: 除了我這房間，大院裏還有二十多間房呢。

sentences.english: Indeed, over the past two decades, the family has dramatically reduced its stake.
sentences.chinese: 過去二十多年來，班氏家族一直在減持股份。

sentences.english: The life of Shubert has altogether created more than 20 piano sonatas.
sentences.chinese: 舒伯特一生共創作了二十多首鋼琴奏鳴曲。

sentences.english: This article has over twenty exclamatory sentences in a row.
sentences.chinese: 這篇文章一連用了二十多個感嘆句。

sentences.english: China a spared more than two billion yuan for the fight against SARA.
sentences.chinese: 爲抗非典，中國撥出了二十多億人民幣。

sentences.chinese: 那時北京有二十多家琴行，她就一家一家上門去應聘。

sentences.english: Throughout his settlement in Paris for over 20 years, Dai Haiying has always been an extremely serious artist.
sentences.chinese: 二十多年定居巴黎，戴海鷹是極認真的畫家。

sentences.english: Twenty years has passed since Tangshan was hit by earthquake.
sentences.chinese: 唐山遭受地震以來二十多年已經過去了。

sentences.english: The long line of soldiers and horse and cannon stretched for twenty miles.
sentences.chinese: 大隊人馬和大炮綿延二十多英里。

sentences.english: The law was held in abeyance for well over twenty years.
sentences.chinese: 這項法律被擱置了二十多年。

sentences.english: During his life, he saw the sale of more than twenty million of his ant colonies.
sentences.chinese: 在他的一生中，他看到了二十多萬，他蟻羣出售。

sentences.english: The choice of Wuhan as the site of the first new U.
sentences.chinese: 美國在武漢設立二十多年來第一個新領館有幾個原因。
